The mechanism for making variables available to all templates in Django is through context processors. Context processors are Python functions that automatically add variables to the template context for every template rendered with RequestContext. They take an HttpRequest object as input and return a dictionary of key-value pairs that get merged into the template context.
column3:
How do I make a variable available to all my templates?

Sometimes your templates all need the same thing. A common example would be dynamically generated menus. At first glance, it seems logical to add a common dictionary to the template context.

The best way to do this in Django is to use a RequestContext. Details on how to do this are here: Using RequestContext.

How do I make a variable available to all my templates?
=======================================================

Sometimes your templates all need the same thing. A common example would be
dynamically generated menus. At first glance, it seems logical to add a common
dictionary to the template context.

The best way to do this in Django is to use a ``RequestContext``. Details on
